
 Book 1: Absolute Basics (From 0 Knowledge)

1. What Is PowerShell?
	•	Shell vs GUI
	•	Cmdlets, objects, and why it's not just another terminal

2. Getting Started
	•	Opening PowerShell
	•	PowerShell vs Windows PowerShell vs PowerShell Core (⭐)
	•	Updating and versions (`$PSVersionTable`)
3. Using the Help System
	•	`Get-Help`, `Update-Help`
	•	How to learn new commands (`Get-Command`, `Get-Member`)

4. Navigating the Filesystem
	•	`Get-Location`, `Set-Location`, `Push-Location`, `Pop-Location` (⭐)
	•	`Get-ChildItem`, `New-Item`, `Remove-Item`, `Move-Item`

5. Reading & Writing to Files
	•	`Get-Content`, `Set-Content`, `Add-Content`
	•	Basic file input/output scripting

6. User Input & Output
	•	`Read-Host`, `Write-Output`, `Write-Host`

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 Book 2: Core Scripting Concepts

1. Variables & Data Types
	•	Strings, integers, arrays, booleans, hashtables (⭐)

2. Operators
	•	Arithmetic (`+`, `-`, etc.)
	•	Comparison (`-eq`, `-ne`, etc.)
	•	Logical (`-and`, `-or`, `-not`)
	•	Type-checking (`-is`, `-as`) ⭐

3. Conditional Logic
	•	`if`, `elseif`, `else`
	•	`switch`

4. Loops & Iteration
	•	`for`, `foreach`, `while`, `do-while`
	•	Breaking and continuing (`break`, `continue`)

5. Functions
	•	Creating functions
	•	Parameters (with validation attributes ⭐)
	•	Returning values

6. Pipelines & Filtering
	•	Sending data with `|`
	•	`Where-Object`, `Select-Object`, `Sort-Object`, `Measure-Object` (⭐)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 Book 3: Intermediate Scripting & Modules

1. Error Handling
	•	`try`, `catch`, `finally`
	•	`$ErrorActionPreference`, `-ErrorAction`, `-ErrorVariable`

2. Advanced Objects
	•	Creating `[PSCustomObject]`
	•	Working with hashtables and nested data
	•	Object properties and methods

3. Working with Dates & Times ⭐
	•	`Get-Date`, date math, formatting

4. Working with Arrays & Loops Together ⭐
	•	Filtering, mapping, reducing

5. Creating and Using Modules
	•	`Import-Module`, `Export-ModuleMember`
	•	Manifest files (`.psd1`) basics

6. Background Jobs & Remoting
	•	`Start-Job`, `Receive-Job`
	•	`Invoke-Command`, `Enter-PSSession`

7. Scheduled Tasks & Task Scheduler
	•	Creating automated tasks from scripts
	•	Logging task output

