4. PowerShell & .NET Integration
	•	Using .NET classes
	•	Calling .NET methods (e.g., `[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText()`)

5. Writing Unit Tests with Pester
	•	Writing test scripts
	•	Test-driven development with PowerShell

6. Creating GUIs (Optional)
	•	WinForms or WPF basics
	•	Simple input and message box examples

7. Git & GitHub Integration
	•	Basic Git workflow
	•	Publishing scripts and modules
	•	GitHub Actions for PowerShell (⭐)

8. Performance Tuning & Logging
	•	`Measure-Command`, `$PROFILE`, transcript logs
